  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "To link your Aadhaar card with SBI (State Bank of India), you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Offline Method:\n- Visit your nearest SBI branch\n- Carry original Aadhaar card and other necessary documents\n- Fill out the Aadhaar linking form\n- Submit the form with required documents\n- Bank representative will verify and link your Aadhaar\n\n2. Online Method:\n- Log in to SBI Internet Banking\n- Go to 'Profile' or 'Personal Banking' section\n- Select 'Aadhaar Linking'\n- Enter Aadhaar details\n- Submit for verification\n\n3. Through SBI Branch ATM:\n- Insert your SBI debit card\n- Select 'Aadhaar Linking' option\n- Follow on-screen instructions\n- Complete linking process\n\n4. Through SBI Mobile App:\n- Open SBI YONO/Mobile Banking app\n- Log in to your account\n- Navigate to profile/settings\n- Select Aadhaar linking option\n- Enter required details\n\nRequired Documents:\n- Original Aadhaar card\n- SBI account details\n- Photograph\n- Address proof\n\nNote: Always carry original documents for verification.",
